/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: credentialless

# COEP = `credentialless` (not `require-corp`). Both keep the page
# cross-origin-ISOLATED so SharedArrayBuffer / Faust WASM threads work
# (crossOriginIsolated === true under either), but `require-corp` BLOCKS every
# cross-origin no-cors subresource that lacks a Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy
# header, whereas `credentialless` loads such subresources without credentials
# and does NOT require CORP. That is what lets ARCHIVIST actually PLAY
# archive.org <video>/<audio> + load <img>: archive.org's CDN sends neither CORP
# nor (reliably) CORS on the final hop, so under require-corp the media was
# blocked outright (never reaching even the tainted-texture stage). A no-cors
# media element is still opaque to the canvas under credentialless, so the
# documented play-only / no-clean-video-texture limitation is unchanged.
# Keep this in sync with packages/web/src/hooks.server.ts (dev) +
# packages/web/vite.config.ts (vite dev/preview).

# Same-origin subresources don't need CORP under credentialless (CORP only gates
# cross-origin), but this stays as belt-and-suspenders for any UA that still
# defaults same-origin embeds — harmless for hashed assets.
/_app/immutable/*
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-site
